<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge" />

    <title>Faker GraphQL</title>

    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="manifest" href="/site.webmanifest" />
    <link rel="mask-icon" href="/safari-pinned-tab.svg" color="#5bbad5" />
    <meta name="msapplication-TileColor" content="#da532c" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#ffffff" />

    <title>Faker GraphQL</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A hosted GraphQL API ready to respond to your requests."
    />
    <meta name="author" content="Cerino O. Ligutom III (ZeferiniXâ„¢)" />
    <meta
      name="keywords"
      content="JavaScript, NodeJS, Faker, GraphQL, Cerino, Ligutom, zeferinix"
    />

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./stylesheets/style.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./stylesheets/bootstrap.min.css" />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.7.2/css/all.css"
      integrity="sha384-fnmOCqbTlWIlj8LyTjo7mOUStjsKC4pOpQbqyi7RrhN7udi9RwhKkMHpvLbHG9Sr"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <section class="welcome">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="brand">
          <h3 class="brand-name">Faker GraphQL</h3>
        </div>

        <hr class="white-separator" />

        <h3 class="heading">Test your front-end against a real GraphQL API</h3>
        <div class="row highlights">
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="info-card">
              <div class="icon-container arrow_box">
                <i class="fas fa-cloud-download-alt"></i>
              </div>

              <div class="details">
                <h5>Fake data</h5>
                <p>
                  Data are auto generated with
                  <span class="emphasize">Faker.js</span> daily.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="info-card">
              <div class="icon-container arrow_box">
                <i class="fas fa-user-lock"></i>
              </div>

              <div class="details">
                <h5>Authentication</h5>
                <p>
                  Practice with protected endpoints using
                  <span class="emphasize">JWT</span>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="info-card">
              <div class="icon-container arrow_box">
                <i class="far fa-clock"></i>
              </div>

              <div class="details">
                <h5>High availability</h5>
                <p>
                  <span class="emphasize">24/7 free access</span> for your
                  development needs.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h4 class="heading">
          A hosted GraphQL API ready to respond to your requests.
        </h4>

        <div class="get-started-button-container">
          <a href="<%= graphqlEndpoint %>"
            ><button class="get-started-button">Try the GraphQL Playground</button></a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="api-details">
      <div class="container">
        <h3 class="heading">API Details</h3>
        <hr />

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="info-card">
              <div class="icon-container">
                <i class="fas fa-cloud"></i>
              </div>

              <h6>Hosted on <span class="emphasize">Vultr</span></h6>

              <p>
                Which means it's a guaranteed reliable platform. The API is CORS enabled. All you
                need to do is send POST requests to:
              </p>

              <code>
                <%= graphqlEndpoint %>
              </code>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="info-card">
              <div class="icon-container">
                <i class="fab fa-github"></i>
              </div>

              <h6>Open-source on GitHub</h6>

              <p>
                Feel free to submit a pull request to propose changes and add
                more endpoints!
              </p>

              <code>
                <%= githubRepositoryUrl %>
              </code>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="peace-of-mind">
      <div class="container">
        <h3 class="heading">Peace of mind</h3>
        <hr />

        <p>
          You might think it's weird to be sending your data to a 3rd party API,
          but I assure you, this API
          <span class="emphasize"
            >does not store any of your data permanently</span
          >. Every midnight, server time, the database is wiped and seeded again
          with the help of <span class="emphasize">Faker.js</span>.
        </p>

        <p>
          All of the source code is open on
          <a href="<%= githubRepositoryUrl %>">GitHub</a> so feel free to check
          the implementation yourself and for your peace of mind.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="footer">
      <div class="container">
        <hr />
        <p>
          Created by
          <a href="<%= zeferinixSiteUrl %>"
            >Cerino O. Ligutom III (ZeferiniX)</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>
